theorem infinite_of_char_zero (R A : Type _) [CommRing R] [IsDomain R] [Ring A] [algebra R A] [CharZero A] :
    { x : A | is_algebraic R x }.infinite :=
  infinite_of_injective_forall_mem Nat.cast_injective is_algebraic_nat
#align infinite_of_char_zero infinite_of_char_zero
countable:
@[simp]
protected theorem countable : set.countable { x : A | is_algebraic R x } :=
  by
  rw [← le_aleph_0_iff_set_countable, ← lift_le]
  apply (cardinal_mk_lift_le_max R A).trans
  simp
#align countable countable

cardinal_mk_lift_of_infinite:

theorem cardinal_mk_lift_of_infinite [Infinite R] :
    cardinal.lift.{u} (cardinal.mk { x : A // is_algebraic R x }) = cardinal.lift.{v} (cardinal.mk R) :=
  ((cardinal_mk_lift_le_max R A).trans_eq (max_eq_left <| aleph_0_le_mk _)).antisymm <|
    lift_mk_le'.2
      ⟨⟨fun x => ⟨algebra_map R A x, is_algebraic_algebra_map _⟩, fun x y h =>
          no_zero_smul_divisors.algebra_map_injective R A (subtype.ext_iff.1 h)⟩⟩

cardinal_mk_lift_le_mul:
/- ./././Mathport/Syntax/Translate/Expr.lean:207:4: warning: unsupported notation `«expr ⁻¹' » -/
/- ./././Mathport/Syntax/Translate/Expr.lean:207:4: warning: unsupported notation `cardinal.mk -/
/- ./././Mathport/Syntax/Translate/Expr.lean:207:4: warning: unsupported notation `cardinal.mk -/
/- ./././Mathport/Syntax/Translate/Expr.lean:207:4: warning: unsupported notation `polynomial -/
/- ./././Mathport/Syntax/Translate/Expr.lean:207:4: warning: unsupported notation `cardinal.aleph_0 -/
theorem cardinal_mk_lift_le_mul :
    cardinal.lift.{u} (cardinal.mk { x : A // is_algebraic R x }) ≤
      cardinal.lift.{v} (cardinal.mk (polynomial R)) * cardinal.aleph_0 :=
  by
  rw [← mk_ulift, ← mk_ulift]
  choose g hg₁ hg₂ using fun x : { x : A | is_algebraic R x } => x.coe_prop
  refine' lift_mk_le_lift_mk_mul_of_lift_mk_preimage_le g fun f => _
  rw [lift_le_aleph_0, le_aleph_0_iff_set_countable]
  suffices : maps_to coe («expr ⁻¹' » g {f}) (f.root_set A)
  exact this.countable_of_inj_on (subtype.coe_injective.inj_on _) (f.root_set_finite A).countable
  rintro x (rfl : g x = f)
  exact mem_root_set.2 ⟨hg₁ x, hg₂ x⟩
#align cardinal_mk_lift_le_mul cardinal_mk_lift_le_mul

/- ./././Mathport/Syntax/Translate/Expr.lean:207:4: warning: unsupported notation `cardinal.mk -/

/- ./././Mathport/Syntax/Translate/Expr.lean:207:4: warning: unsupported notation `cardinal.aleph_0 -/
theorem cardinal_mk_lift_le_max :
    cardinal.lift.{u} (cardinal.mk { x : A // is_algebraic R x }) ≤
      max (cardinal.lift.{v} (cardinal.mk R)) (cardinal.aleph_0) :=
  (cardinal_mk_lift_le_mul R A).trans <| (mul_le_mul_right' (lift_le.2 cardinal_mk_le_max) _).trans <| by simp
#align cardinal_mk_lift_le_max cardinal_mk_lift_le_max

aleph_0_le_cardinal_mk_of_char_zero:
/- ./././Mathport/Syntax/Translate/Expr.lean:207:4: warning: unsupported notation `cardinal.aleph_0 -/
/- ./././Mathport/Syntax/Translate/Expr.lean:207:4: warning: unsupported notation `cardinal.mk -/
theorem aleph_0_le_cardinal_mk_of_char_zero (R A : Type _) [CommRing R] [IsDomain R] [Ring A] [algebra R A]
    [CharZero A] : cardinal.aleph_0 ≤ cardinal.mk { x : A // is_algebraic R x } :=
  infinite_iff.1 (set.infinite_coe_iff.2 <| infinite_of_char_zero R A)
#align aleph_0_le_cardinal_mk_of_char_zero aleph_0_le_cardinal_mk_of_char_zero
